drawing =/= 3d modeling
In 3d, you only have to do everything once in order to mass produce a bunch of images. You only need to make one model (20% of your time) and you need to texture it (80% of your time). Once you are done, you can pose and put it in any environment with infinite amount of possibilities and combinations, and it is way easier than drawing. Because you have to draw each individual image by hand instead of opening a file, messing around for a bit, and clicking the render button.

Just go on youtube and look at blender tutorials. You'd be surprised on the number of photo-realistic things you can make in two hours at the most. Blender tutorials are much easier that learning to draw.
